    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin avoids bots posting comments directly on your site.</p>\n<h4>How to use</h4>\n<p>After installing and activating the plugin, go to Settings-&gt;General and enter your unique <code>Combat Comment Bot Secret Key</code></p>\n<h4>How it Works</h4>\n<p>This plugin adds <a href=\"http://markjaquith.wordpress.com/2006/06/02/wordpress-203-nonces/\" title=\"nonces\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">nonces</a> using the secret key to the comment form for unique validation.</p>\n<h4>Feedback &amp; Question</h4>\n<p>For questions or suggestions, tweet us <a href=\"http://twitter.com/revood\" title=\"@revood\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">@revood</a></p>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>Does it protect against spam?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>No, this plugin only keeps bots from posting comments.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release</li>\n</ul>\n"
